   <head>EPIGRAM VIII. On Mrs. PENELOPE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">THE gentle Pen with look demure,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Awhile was thought a virgin pure:</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But Pen, as ancient poets say,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Undid by night the work of day.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
